  "prompt": "How many people have a net worth of 20 million dollars?",
  "response": "Determining the exact number of people with a net worth of 20 million dollars is challenging due to the constantly changing nature of wealth, variations in market conditions, and privacy considerations. Wealth estimates are typically provided in broader categories rather than specific net worth figures. For instance, wealth reports categorize individuals as millionaires, multi-millionaires, or billionaires.\n\nAccording to wealth reports from organizations like Credit Suisse or Capgemini, the number of high-net-worth individuals (HNWIs), typically defined as those having investable assets of $1 million or more, can provide some context. The number of individuals with a net worth of $20 million would fall somewhere in between their standard millionaire and ultra-high-net-worth individual (UHNWI) categories.\n\nOverall, it's important to refer to the latest global wealth distribution reports or surveys for the most accurate and updated information.",
